<p>&quot;What do you-&quot; Judas winced as the Witness bent his legs as if helping him stand back up, prompting his nerves to complete the move and subsequently scream as hard as they could. &quot;<em>Fuck</em>, fuck, you can't just, just tell me to hide if you-&quot;</p>
<p>And like an air-powered robot (minus the air and plus the Witness), Judas was walking on screaming legs across the room and towards a blinds-obscured closet. It was almost enough to make him forget that his arms and head <em>also</em> existed, though the difference between leaning against the door and a (thankfully theoretical) concussion left the ever-increasing scraping sounds that much clearer.</p>
